## 📋 AI Copyright Compliance Checklist

### Before Fine-Tuning or RAG Index Building

- [ ] **TDM opt-out scan**: All documents in the corpus scanned for Art. 4 opt-outs
- [ ] **Opt-out exclusion log**: Excluded documents logged for transparency report
- [ ] **License inventory**: All document licenses recorded (clear / restricted / blocked)
- [ ] **Lawful access verification**: System has lawful access to all included content
- [ ] **Art. 53(1)(d) summary**: Training data summary prepared for disclosure

### Before Inference (Per-Request)

- [ ] **Copyright pre-check**: `CopyrightChecker.check_documents()` runs before any LLM call
- [ ] **BLOCKED doc gate**: Hard stop implemented — BLOCKED docs never reach LLM
- [ ] **RESTRICTED instruction**: Paraphrase instruction injected into system prompt
- [ ] **Source citation instruction**: Every LLM call includes attribution requirement

### After Inference (Per-Response)

- [ ] **Output validation**: Verify no verbatim text from RESTRICTED docs
- [ ] **AI disclosure**: AI-generated output labeled as AI-generated (EU AI Act Art. 50)
- [ ] **Audit log**: Log `processing_id`, documents used, copyright statuses per call
- [ ] **Usage log**: Record inference call in `ai_usage_logs` for quota and audit

---

## 🚨 High-Risk Practices to Avoid

- **NEVER** fine-tune a GPAI model on documents with Art. 4 opt-outs without first obtaining a license
- **NEVER** index BLOCKED documents into a vector database or RAG system
- **NEVER** present AI-generated summaries of RESTRICTED content without paraphrase validation
- **NEVER** allow GPAI output to reproduce verbatim passages from RESTRICTED documents
- **NEVER** omit AI disclosure in user-facing content (EU AI Act Art. 50)
- **NEVER** claim copyright on purely AI-generated text in system responses
